$ VBA - language: keyword isMissing

`isMissing()` is a → development/languages/VBA/functions[VBA function] to check if an → development/languages/VBA/language/subs-and-functions/optional-parameters[optional parameter] was given a value.

Unfortunately, it does not distinguish between passing → development/languages/VBA/language/null-and-nothing-etc[`null`] or not explicitely stating a value.

The → /development/languages/VBA/language/datatypes of a → development/languages/VBA/language/subs-and-functions/parameters that needs to be checked with `isMissing()` needs to be a → /development/languages/VBA/language/datatypes/variant.

